comments:
On 25.3.1885 the Devon part of the parish of Exmoor became 
    part of the parish of North Molton, so that thereafter Exmoor was wholly in 
    Somerset. See also Table 2, notes (a) and (e).

Created 1894 from the rural part of the parish of South Molton. 
    See also Table 2, note (f).
Abolished 1894 and added to the parish of Satterleigh & Warkleigh.

Created 1894 from the separate parishes of Warkleigh and Satterleigh. 
    See also Table 2, note (f).
Abolished 1894 and added to the parish of Satterleigh & Warkleigh.
Abolished 25.3.1885 and added to the parish of West Worlington.
